data.chText: 不让步的；不妥协的；强硬的
data.enText: unwilling to change your opinions or behaviour

data.chText: 他的严厉和强硬态度是出了名的。
data.enText: He has a reputation for being tough and uncompromising.

example: took an uncompromising stance in the peace talks

value.def: If you describe someone as uncompromising, you mean that they are determined not to change their opinions or aims in any way.

example.ex: Mrs Thatcher was a tough and uncompromising politician.
example.tran: 撒切尔夫人是一位态度强硬、不轻易妥协的政治家。

value.tran: 不妥协的；不让步的；坚定的

example.ex: The company had once been uncompromisingly socialist...
example.tran: 该公司曾一度坚定地走社会主义道路。

example.ex: He states uncompromisingly that he is opposed to any practices which oppress animals.
example.tran: 他坚决声明反对任何虐待动物的行为。

value.def: If you describe something as uncompromising, you mean that it does not attempt to make something that is shocking or unpleasant any more acceptable to people.
